fields.description: Describes how the conditional access authentication context was triggered. A value of previouslySatisfied means the auth context was because the user already satisfied the requirements for that authentication context in some previous authentication event. A value of required means the user had to meet the authentication context requirement as part of the sign-in flow. The possible values are: required, previouslySatisfied, notApplicable, unknownFutureValue.
